      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIDNIGHT ALIBI (11) went back last start then worked home in good style to finish 4 metres from the winner in third at Swan Hill. May just need a bit of luck from this difficult draw but she should strip fitter so can continue the strong start to the campaign. PARINI (2) lines up for the first time. By The Storm Inside and hails from the Stephen O'Donoghue stable. Should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position so could kick off with a win. MAJOR ORION (6) made a solid impact on debut eight days ago at Swan Hill, finishing second and beaten just a head after leading and fighting on well. Draws wider but is open to natural improvement so could go one better. MIDNIGHT DIVA (1) is a possible improver after debuting with a solid third from this barrier at Swan Hill.",
